Bring a large #saucepan of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes. Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, quartered lengthways and chopped into small pieces), then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Roughly chop the @sliced mushrooms{120%g}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled) into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan on high heat. Once hot, add the chopped carrot and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and mushrooms to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until the veg is softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the veg has softened, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1/2%carton}, @mushroom broth paste{15%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @dried rosemary{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} to the pan. Bring to the boil, then stir through the lentils. Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add half the @butter{30%g} and a splash of milk (if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt.

Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the pie filling has thickened, taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Top with an even layer of mash and sprinkle over the cheese. Grill until the cheese is bubbling and golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, clean the (now empty) frying pan and pop back on medium heat with the remaining butter. Once melted, add the @peas{120%g} and stir until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

When the pie is ready, serve on plates with the buttery peas alongside. Enjoy!